# Interpretation block

- "Longer windows resolve ringing broadly" if SEQ_LEN=372 reduces mean severe-failure |err| by >70% AND overall RMSE drops >20%
- "Longer windows partially resolve ringing" if severe-failure |err| drops 30-70% or overall RMSE drops 10-20%
- "Length alone insufficient" if severe-failure |err| drops <30% even at SEQ_LEN=400 — in which case state-carrier features (Prompt 10b) are required
- "Diminishing returns at p75" if SEQ_LEN=372 and 400 are within 2% RMSE of SEQ_LEN=325 — means 325 is the efficient choice going forward
- Flag separately: if overall RMSE worsens at SEQ_LEN=400 compared to SEQ_LEN=372, report as "saturation + overfit" and note that GRU capacity is being spent on noise past the p95 lookback

# Requirements

- Print VRAM peak per config. At SEQ_LEN=400 with batch 64 and 4 GRU layers × 64 hidden, should be well under 8 GB but worth measuring.
- Use identical train/val/test splits — do not re-fit the scaler.
- If any config fails to converge in 200 epochs, report it and move on rather than retrying with more epochs. Convergence failure IS a result.
- The idx=38180 error column must be computed on the SAME test sample index across all configs (i.e., the sample at global test-split position 38180, regardless of how the window construction changes around it).

# Deliverables

1. The sweep report with both tables and interpretation.
2. Training curves for all 4 new configs + baseline on one plot (5 curves, coloured by SEQ_LEN).
3. A plot of mean severe-failure |err| vs SEQ_LEN (5 points). This is the single most informative figure for the thesis — it directly answers "how much does lookback help?"
4. A plot of prediction vs truth over samples 38150-38250 for baseline and SEQ_LEN=372 overlaid. Should make the improvement (or lack thereof) visually obvious.

# Deliverables applicable to all prompts

1. Short summary of the purpose of the prompt and the interpretation/implication of the verdict, appended to `prompts/SUMMARY+CONCLUSION.txt`.

# Out of scope

- MLP — input dimension blowup makes this apples-to-oranges.
- Feature changes — that's Prompt 10b.
- Hyperparameter tuning per SEQ_LEN — isolate the effect of sequence length.
- Combining longer windows with residual learning (Prompt 10) — combinations come after single-variable sweeps.